    "attributes": {
        "action": "Reform the Bereavement Notification System for Government Services",
        "additional_details": "I urge the government to review and reform the bereavement notification system. Implement a more efficient, compassionate, and user-friendly process to alleviate undue stress on grieving families. Prioritise digital solutions, improve inter-departmental communication, and ensure prompt resolution of financial matters to prevent additional burdens during a challenging period. Develop a true - Tell us Once service.",
        "background": "I want the Government to conduct a review of theTell us Once service. I don't believe that the current service is living up to its intention of providing a streamlined service. I seek reform for a compassionate and streamlined process during times of grief.",
